title: For Sale:  COLT 1943 Issue 1911A1 - Mint
postcontent: Colt manufactured 1911A1 issued in 1943 to USAAF Navigator who flew in B-17's and 24's in No. Africa, Europe and finally ASW missions out of Iceland.  This pistol was fam fired or shot for qualification, but that's it.  Everything about it is museum quality.  All markings on slide and frame are correct, including lightly struck Ordnance Stamp behind left grip at top.  I've tried to get as much detail as possible in close up photos.  Smaller marks include "P" just behind magazine release and on top of slide forward of rear sight.  There are also capital letters "GHD" on left side of frame between trigger cut and grip.  There is a very small "W" and triangle at the top of the trigger guard on the left side, and a "21" at the same place on the right.  Brown plastic grips, lanyard on butt, checkered hammer and trigger, blued barrel and magazine are all correct.  The only mark on the gun is a slight rub from slide on barrel at ejection port, consistent with very limited use.  This Colt is as good as they get, and it comes with Enger-Kress M-3 shoulder holster, also issued to the Navigator above, and in astonishingly good condition for a piece of leather over seventy years old.

title: For Sale:  Slide Fire SSAR-15 SBS Bump Fire Stock AR15 Right Handed
postcontent:
Brand new in box! Up for bid is a Slide Fire SSAR-15 SBS bump fire stock for an AR15. Right Hand. The Slide Fire Solutions SSAR-15 SBS (Standard Battle Stock) Bump Fire Buttstock is the latest iteration of the company's groundbreaking SSAR-15 OGR Original Bump Fire Stock, incorporating the same performance, reliability, and superior craftsmanship of the OGR with a new look designed to appear similar to many of today's popular, modern battle rifle stocks. The SSAR-15 SBS allows the shooter to safely bump fire their AR-15 from the shoulder, effectively and legally simulating fully automatic fire, and allowing for an unprecedented measure of control that is severely lacking when attempting to bump fire a rifle in the traditional, "from-the-hip" manner. The SSAR-15 features a shelf that positions the shooter's index finger in a fixed position in front of the rifle's trigger. To fire, the upper receiver is moved forward with the support hand pushing on the forend, thereby bringing the trigger to the shooter's finger and discharging a round. The rifle's recoil causes the upper receiver to move rearward, allowing the trigger mechanism to reset. When the right amount of constant forward pressure is applied, the rifle will continue to fire as the trigger is brought forward and depressed by the shooter's stationary index finger, causing the gun to Bump Fire. With a little practice, the shooter will be capable of delivering accurate single shots, bursts, or even full magazine dumps on demand using the SSAR-15. The SSAR-15 is designed for installation onto any Mil-Spec Diameter AR-15 Collapsible Stock Receiver Extension Buffer Tube. Installation involves removing the factory pistol grip, replacing it with the included Interface Block, and sliding the SSAR-15 onto the buffer tube. No permanent modifications or gunsmithing required! Each SSAR-15 assembly includes the SBS Buttstock, an Interface Block, Hex Key, Instructions, BATFE Approval Letter and Lifetime Factory Warranty. Made in the USA. Payment I can do a F2F and prefer cash, however if you would like I can ship the item to you if you pay shipping cost. I will accept a USPS money order via mail if we agree on shipping also I accept Paypal if you pay the fees and Credit/Debit card over the phone if you pay the fees.
